<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>When repopulating data on a form through  $form-&gt;populate($formData), the function adds slashes to user input and shows the slashes on the form.</p>

<p>Ex : 
-&gt; I have a Zend_Form with 2 elements a Text element and a submit element
-&gt; I have one validation rule on the Text element requireing 2 characters minimum
-&gt; I enter " on my form and click submit
-&gt; the form returns \"  and an error (please insert 2 characters mini)</p>

<p>Solution : Before repopulating data on the form the function populate should strip the slashes that were added to protect from user input.</p>

